{"accepted":[{"assertion":"Erdős Problem #821: declared status 'open'. Formalized: no. Let $g(n)$ count the number of $m$ such that $\\phi(m)=n$. Is it true that, for every $\\epsilon>0$, there exist infinitely many $n$ such that\\[g(n) > n^{1-\\epsilon}?\\] Current best: The best known bound is that there are infinitely many $n$ such that\\[g(n) > n^{0.71568\\cdots},\\]obtained by Lichtman \\cite{Li22} as a consequence of proving that there are $\\geq \\frac{x}{(\\log x)^{O(1)}}$ many primes $p\\leq x$ such that all prime factors of $p-1$ are $\\leq x^{0.2843\\cdots}$ (which improves a number of previous exponents, most recently Baker and Harman \\cite{BaHa98}). Prize: no. OEIS: A014197. Tags: number theory.","id":"vf_41c918430f227c27","trust":"signed","type":"theoretical"},{"assertion":"Formal-Conjectures statement: Erdos821.erdos_821 https://google-deepmind.github.io/formal-conjectures/theorem/?name=Erdos821.erdos_821.","id":"vf_4adee5f7c8af0cf5","trust":"signed","type":"theoretical"}],"accepted_activity":false,"activity":[],"activity_types":[],"attempt_count":0,"banked_attempt_count":0,"commits":[],"dependency_impact":"none","detail_url":"problems/821.json","draft_proposals":[],"edges":[{"evidence":"Problem identity derived from the accepted finding's pinned source anchor.","inferred":true,"relation":"describes","source":"vf_41c918430f227c27","source_root":"sha256:1faedc24f040a60a22177b456c74b969a61ce8836082297b1835797a57b4fa56","target":"erdos:821","trust":"signed"},{"evidence":"Problem identity derived from the accepted finding's pinned source anchor.","inferred":true,"relation":"describes","source":"vf_4adee5f7c8af0cf5","source_root":"sha256:1faedc24f040a60a22177b456c74b969a61ce8836082297b1835797a57b4fa56","target":"erdos:821","trust":"signed"},{"evidence":"Materialized typed link between accepted findings.","inferred":true,"relation":"synthesized_from","source":"vf_4adee5f7c8af0cf5","source_root":"sha256:1faedc24f040a60a22177b456c74b969a61ce8836082297b183579